{"TopicId":191768,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Boeing AH-64D Apache Longbow","CreatedByName":"Yaeah","CreatedById":98009,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-19T08:15:23Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Yaeah","CreatedById":98009,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-19T08:15:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:22px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBoeing AH-64D Apache Longbow\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\nTo control the heli, start by controlling\u00A0the rotor collective with Translate U/D keys I and K. Then, set the throttle to slightly below 1/3.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EParts: \u003C/strong\u003E351\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWeight:\u003C/strong\u003E 23t\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELength: \u003C/strong\u003E13.6m\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETop Speed:\u003C/strong\u003E ~35m/s\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Yaeah/Boeing-AH-64D-Apache-Longbow\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAH-64D on KerbalX\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022FzNtHdf.png?1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/FzNtHdf.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022buAI736.png?1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/buAI736.png?1\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-03T07:42:08Z\u0022 title=\u002203/03/2020 07:42  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 3, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Yaeah\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IkranMakto","CreatedById":198477,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-19T19:17:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022\u041A\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u043D\u043A\u0438 \u043F\u043E \u0437\u0430\u043F\u0440\u043E\u0441\u0443 \u0026quot;apache tail rotor\u0026quot;\u0022 data-ratio=\u002267.22\u0022 width=\u0022729\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.stack.imgur.com/QHYDT.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Yaeah","CreatedById":98009,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-20T02:17:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223743705\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221582139831\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022198477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022IkranMakto\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, IkranMakto said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022\u041A\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u043D\u043A\u0438 \u043F\u043E \u0437\u0430\u043F\u0440\u043E\u0441\u0443 \u0026quot;apache tail rotor\u0026quot;\u0022 data-ratio=\u002267.22\u0022 width=\u0022729\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.stack.imgur.com/QHYDT.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngood catch, changed the tail rotors to contra-rotating\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-20T02:17:31Z\u0022 title=\u002202/20/2020 02:17  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 20, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Yaeah\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"XLjedi","CreatedById":175658,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-20T02:52:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI always thought that was a curiously complex tail rotor for an otherwise conventional attack helo.\u00A0 I remember way back in my high-school model building days, puzzling over why the tail rotor blades that shipped with my 1/48 scale Apache kit were obviously wrong.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-20T03:17:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223743879\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221582165041\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298009\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Yaeah\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n58 minutes ago, Yaeah said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ngood catch, changed the tail rotors to contra-rotating\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey don\u0027t contra-rotate. They\u0027re just set at a non-90-degree angle to avoid radar reflections and reduce its radar cross-section.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut that\u0027s a quibble. It\u0027s an impressive replica. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Yaeah","CreatedById":98009,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-20T03:33:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223743900\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221582168656\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 minutes ago, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey don\u0027t contra-rotate. They\u0027re just set at a non-90-degree angle to avoid radar reflections and reduce its radar cross-section.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut that\u0027s a quibble. It\u0027s an impressive replica. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbruh\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u2019ll have to re-fix it later lmao\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-20T03:40:53Z\u0022 title=\u002202/20/2020 03:40  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 20, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Yaeah\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Raptor9","CreatedById":67915,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-20T04:47:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223743900\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221582168656\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u0027re just set at a non-90-degree angle to avoid radar reflections and reduce its radar cross-section.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure about how it\u00A0affects its radar cross-section, but the primary reason it was designed with a 55-degree separation vs the typical 90-degrees in 4-bladed tail rotors is to increase tail rotor efficiency and performance.\u00A0 The 55-degree separation, coupled with the lateral offset of each blade \u0022pair\u0022 ensures that the second set of blades operates in clean air, instead of operating in the wake of the first pair of blades.\u00A0 It\u0027s like following close and to the side of another aircraft, avoiding it\u0027s wake.\u00A0 However the further back and/or closer to its tail you are, the greater chance you will encounter turbulent air trailing behind its airfoil surfaces, which will expand the further back you go.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother common misconception was that it was designed to make it more quiet.\u00A0 While avoiding the wake of leading pair of blades does lead to less noise, this is a convenient by-product of the aerodynamic design, rather than the primary reason\u00A0for the design implementation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-20T04:48:48Z\u0022 title=\u002202/20/2020 04:48  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 20, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Raptor9\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"XLjedi","CreatedById":175658,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-20T05:23:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich all reaffirms my decision to not build replicas... but that is a fine looking craft.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell done!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Servo","CreatedById":149419,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-21T15:10:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223743939\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221582174074\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002267915\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Raptor9\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/20/2020 at 5:47 AM, Raptor9 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure about how it\u00A0affects its radar cross-section, but the primary reason it was designed with a 55-degree separation vs the typical 90-degrees in 4-bladed tail rotors is to increase tail rotor efficiency and performance.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery interesting - thanks for sharing! Makes me curious then about why such a design isn\u0027t more common. Maybe something to do with mechanical complexity?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223743953\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221582176187\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022175658\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022XLjedi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/20/2020 at 6:23 AM, XLjedi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich all reaffirms my decision to not build replicas... but that is a fine looking craft.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell done!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the contrary, this is the sort of thing I live for when building replicas. You notice a small detail, then you go down a rabbit hole figuring out why that bit made it onto such a highly engineered machine.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDisregarding tail-rotor quibbles, this is a lovely replica! The solar panels really work well here, and the fuselage shaping works really well too.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"XLjedi","CreatedById":175658,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-21T15:21:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149419-servo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022149419\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/149419-servo/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Servo\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0 No, I avoid em because there will always be someone to point out a flaw or better version...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen arguments ensue over who\u0027s replica is the bestest-est-est.\u00A0 I\u0027ve actually seen some people say stuff like, \u0022That\u0027s the best replica I\u0027ve ever seen!\u0022\u00A0 Trying to complement the builder and then 2 or 3 other twits chime in with stuff like \u0022Really?\u00A0 Then you haven\u0027t seen my version: [link], [link], [link]\u0022\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(to be clear, no one has done anything like that on this thread)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...but it can get stupid quick.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-21T15:24:06Z\u0022 title=\u002202/21/2020 03:24  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 21, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by XLjedi\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}